Japanese Prime Minister's Reckless Remarks Accused 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 11 (KCNA) -- The reckless remarks made by Abe openly denying the coercive recruitment of the "comfort women" for the imperial Japanese army are nothing but a crafty and shameful attempt to conceal the Japanese imperialists' crimes against humanity and evade state responsibility for the crimes, an unbearable mockery of the victims of the crimes and their bereaved families and an unpardonable challenge to all the Koreans and other members of the international community urging Japan to make an apology and compensation for them. A spokesman for the Central Committee of the Democratic Front for the Reunification of the Fatherland declared this in a statement issued on Sunday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  His outbursts are nothing but vituperation intended to justify Japan's past crimes and accelerate militarization for reinvasion and most insolent remarks making a mockery of justice and human conscience, the statement noted, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now the whole world is condemning Japan's above-said crimes as the worst flesh traffic in the 20th century and the most hideous sexual slavery unprecedented in history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The prime minister of a country dared again deny the sexual slavery. This clearly indicates how vulgar and shameful the Japanese reactionaries are. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This being a hard reality, Japan dares make a bid for permanent membership of the UN Security Council and pull up the dignified DPRK. Can there be any more hateful and cursed country of brutes than it? &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan coerced hundreds of thousands of Korean women into providing sex to the imperial Japanese army and hurled millions of young and middle-aged Koreans into battle fields and slave labor sites, killing many of them. It is nonsensical, therefore, for the descendents of Samurais to talk about someone's "abduction" and the like. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the Korean people should not pardon this spate of remarks made by the Japanese reactionaries but roundly expose the crimes committed by Japan against the Korean nation and force it to pay for all its wrongdoings.

June 15 All-Korean Committee Meets in China 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 10 (KCNA) -- A meeting of the June 15 All-Korean Committee was held in Shenyang of China on Mar. 8 and 9. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the meeting were a delegation of the North Side Committee for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration headed by its Chairman An Kyong Ho, a delegation of the South Side Committee for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration headed by its Chairman Paek Rak Chong and a delegation of the Overseas Side Committee for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration led by its Co-Chairmen Kwak Tong Ui and Mun Tong Hwan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The meeting referred to the fact that the committee advanced the movement for independent reunification last year and sincerely discussed measures for conducting the reunification movement on the principle of attaching priority to national dignity and interests under the banner of the June 15 joint declaration and waging a more dynamic movement for freeing the country from all war threats and creating a peaceful environment for national reunification this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It underscored the need for the north, the south and the overseas sides to hold the national joint event to mark the seventh anniversary of the publication of the June 15 joint declaration in Pyongyang and August 15 event for reunification in the south side's area and give further momentum to the solidarity movement involving organizations of people in different fields and circles, hold multifarious functions for reunification to be attended by people from all walks of life in the places to be agreed upon and wage a positive movement to set June 15, the historic day the joint declaration was published, as a commemoration day common to the nation on the basis of the shared understanding that the June 15 joint declaration serves as a milestone in the reunification movement this year, too, as they did in the last year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A special statement in the name of the June 15 All-Korean Committee was adopted at the meeting to denounce the Japanese authorities' brutal suppression of Koreans in Japan and their militarist ambition. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It urged the Japanese government to drop its hostile policy towards the DPRK, opt for building a peace-keeping mechanism in Northeast Asia and immediately stop its brutal suppression of Koreans in Japan, a primitive crime. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A joint press release on the results of the meeting of the June 15 All-Korean Committee was made public at the meeting.

Congratulatory Events Held in Italy 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 11 (KCNA) -- A meeting and a study contest were held in Italy on Mar. 3 to congratulate Kim Jong Il upon receiving the "International Kim Il Sung Prize." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Displayed in the venues of the events were Kim Jong Il's famous works and books introducing his undying Songun revolutionary leadership feats. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were figures and people from all walks of life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Miriam Pelegrini Feri, president of the Group of Dialectical Materialists of Italy, in her speech at the meeting said that Kim Jong Il was awarded the "International Kim Il Sung Prize" for the great feats he has performed on behalf of the history of human thoughts by developing in depth the Juche idea founded by President Kim Il Sung and his immortal contributions to accomplishing the noble cause of defending global peace and security and achieving the independent development of humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She noted that the Italian revolutionaries and progressive people extend the warmest congratulations to Kim Jong Il on receiving the prize. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The study contest was held by way of putting questions about different issues and answering them in order to help the attendants deeply grasp the personality of Kim Jong Il as a great man. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those who took the floor highly praised Kim Jong Il as the greatest statesman of the present times, adding that he has firmly defended Korean-style socialism and wisely led the struggle for national reunification, creditably carrying forward the revolutionary cause of Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the Juche idea is an original and scientific revolutionary philosophy, they stressed that socialism in the DPRK where the Juche idea has been embodied is the best socialism for the people and it is a model for other peoples to follow.

Japanese Prime Minister's Reckless Remarks under Fire in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 11 (KCNA) -- The south Korean political circles have accused the Japanese prime minister of letting loose a spate of reckless remarks intended to evade the responsibility for the past sexual slavery, according to the south Korean MBC and CBS. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that Abe let loose outbursts that there is no evidence proving the coercive recruitment of the "comfort women" for the imperial Japanese army, the "lawmakers' society for national spirit" in its statement on Mar. 3 declared he can neither play down nor conceal the Japanese imperialists' crimes related to the "comfort women" just as he cannot get the sun eclipsed by his palms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the same day, the spokesperson for the "Uri Party" lambasted the Japanese prime minister for making insolent remarks, instead of honestly repenting of the crimes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The spokesman for the "Democratic Party" asserted that there is no future for Japan as it does not sincerely reflect on its past wrongdoings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Lawmakers affiliated to the "reformists' society of the Uri Party" at a press conference on Mar. 6 charged that Japan had better sincerely apologize for the wrongs it committed in the past and make practical efforts for the world peace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the "Ministry of Foreign Affairs and Trade" noted in its commentary on Mar. 3 that Abe's reckless remarks are aimed to twist the historical truth, demanding Japan have a correct understanding of its history.

Japanese Imperialists' Suppression of Struggle for National Liberation Disclosed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 11 (KCNA) -- After illegally occupying Korea the Japanese imperialists revised the penalty rules of the "Maintenance of the Public Order Act", Japan's fascist domestic law, to make it better serve the purpose of their fascist colonial rule over Korea and, on this basis, enacted various special criminal laws such as the "Law on the Supervision over Korean Political Criminals for Public Peace" and the "Law on the Preventive Detention of Korean Political Criminals," mercilessly cracking down upon Koreans' anti-Japanese national liberation struggle. Rodong Sinmun Sunday observes this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan applied the "Maintenance of the Public Order Act" to suppressing the national liberation struggle in other country. This was an unjustifiable criminal act in view of international law. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a publicly accepted principle governing the international relations to disallow any measure and action to be taken to suppress and restrict by force of arms the right of each country and nation to sovereignty and independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The indelible crimes the Japanese imperialists committed against the Korean people by faking up and enforcing such fascist laws as the above-said act can never be tolerated no matter how often an old generation is replaced by a new one. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nevertheless, the Japanese reactionaries have added to their crimes up to this date since the defeat of the Japanese imperialists, far from making any apology and compensation to the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is evidenced by the fact that last year they became more desperate than ever before in their crackdown upon the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon), an overseas citizens organization of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their suppression of Chongryon has become unprecedented since the outset of this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is a wanton violation of international law and inhumane and fascist brutality. Their reckless suppression and terrorism against Chongryon and Koreans in Japan are a repetition of the Japanese imperialists' brutal crackdown upon the Korean people's anti-Japanese national liberation struggle and little short of committing double or treble crimes against the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people will surely force Japan to pay for its hideous past crimes.

Japanese Government Urged to Make Apology and Compensation  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 11 (KCNA) -- Members of women's organizations including the Women's Solidarity of south Korea and victims of the "comfort women" for the imperial Japanese army reportedly held the 751st Wednesday meeting in front of the Japanese embassy in Seoul on March 7 to rap the reckless remarks made by the Japanese prime minister. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Attendants of the meeting expressed their anger at Japanese Prime Minister Abe for unhesitatingly asserting recently that there is no evidence proving the forcible recruitment of "comfort women," Japan cannot be responsible for the crimes and the like. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These brazen-faced outbursts made by him were intended to distort history and cause unbearable double pain and wounds to the victims, they added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They urged Abe to immediately retract his reckless remarks and make a formal apology and compensation for Japan's past crimes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They stated all the women in this land would not stop the struggle till they wrest the apology and compensation from the Japanese government.

Movement for Peace against War Called for in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 11 (KCNA) -- Youth and students organizations of south Korea including the Students Committee of the Democratic Labor Party reportedly called a joint press conference in front of the U.S. military base in Ryongsan on March 6 at which they declared that all the youths and students would turn out in the movement for peace against war in order to frustrate the moves of the U.S. and the south Korea military authorities to stage war exercises for aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the conference termed the RSOI planned by them war maneuvers aimed at fighting an all-out war according to their scenario for mounting a preemptive attack on the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said saber-rattling planned by them at a time when dialogue and negotiations are under way to put an end to confrontation and defuse the war crisis on the Korean Peninsula and bring durable peace to it glaringly reveal the U.S. ambition to stifle the north, they charged.

Need to Foil Imperialists' Campaign for Ideological and Cultural Poisoning Underscored 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 11 (KCNA) -- A revolutionary ideological offensive is very important for frustrating the evermore undisguised psychological warfare and campaign for ideological and cultural poisoning being escalated by the U.S. imperialists and class enemies, consolidating the unity of the revolutionary ranks in thinking and purpose in every way and giving full play to the dynamism of the political and ideological power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Sunday observes this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  It goes on: The socialist construction is now under way in the DPRK amidst a fierce struggle against the U.S. imperialists and class enemies. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists are desperate in their psychological warfare and campaign for ideological and cultural poisoning aimed at destabilizing Korean-style socialism. It is the black-hearted intention of the U.S. imperialists to achieve by dint of "flexible strategy" of ideological and cultural poisoning the sinister aim they failed to do through their political and military pressure and the force of arms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the avowed principled stand of the Workers' Party of Korea to foil the enemies' psychological warfare and campaign for ideological and cultural poisoning through a revolutionary ideological offensive. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists are now clinging to such a foolish method, aware that they can hardly bring down Korean-style socialism as long as all the servicepersons and people remain single-mindedly united around the headquarters of the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists knocked into shape a lot of organizations for psychological warfare with all sorts of good-for-nothings such as reactionary professors and writers who are skillful in hatching all sorts of plots and employing gimmicks and depraved and corrupt artistes, psychologists and historians. They spend hundreds of millions of dollars for this warfare and conduct smear campaigns against the DPRK in a sinister and foolish bid to sever the blood ties among the WPK, the leader and the army and the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Only when every psychological warfare and campaign for ideological and cultural poisoning launched by them are frustrated, is it possible to prevent any unsound ideological factor from finding its way to society, augment the might of the single-minded unity and emerge victorious in the confrontation with enemies, the article concludes.

Kim Jong Il's Work Published in Italy
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 10 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il's famous work "Let Us Carry Out the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung's Instructions for National Reunification" was brought out in booklet by a printing house of Italy on Feb. 16. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work, published on August 4, Juche 86 (1997), deals with the undying feats President Kim Il Sung performed for the cause of national reunification, formulates the three principles of national reunification, the proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo and the ten-point programme for the great unity of the whole nation as the three charters for national reunification and clarifies the tasks and ways for achieving the cause of Korea's reunification based on them.

Asian Regional Seminar Held in Sri Lanka
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 10 (KCNA) -- The Asian regional seminar on self-reliance, national economy and the cause of independence was held in Colombo on Feb. 27. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was attended by the director general and the secretary general of the Asian Regional Institute of the Juche Idea and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The delegation of the Korean Social Scientists Society was on hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 W. A. Duminduwardane, first vice-chairman of the Committee of Self-Reliance Studies (Juche) in Sri Lanka, in his congratulatory speech said that the DPRK has won one victory after another despite the U.S. anti-DPRK moves by thoroughly adhering to the principle of self-reliance under the uplifted banner of the Juche idea, the Songun idea, adding that it is important to use the seminar as a good opportunity to find the way of learning from the experience of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Reggie Ranatunge, director general of the Asian Regional Institute of the Juche Idea, in his report noted that it is the common duty of the world progressive people to build an independent country as the Korean people do. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that the self-reliance of the DPRK is based on the Juche idea which was founded by President Kim Il Sung and has been developed in depth by leader Kim Jong Il, he explained and proved the truth, scientific accuracy and tremendous vitality of the Juche idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Harish Gupta, secretary general of the Asian Regional Institute of the Juche Idea, and other speakers called upon the Asian countries to hold higher the banner of independence and self-reliance, adding that it is imperative to check and frustrate the U.S. moves for "globalization" to build powerful national economy and realize the cause of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A letter to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the seminar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The letter noted that the recent miraculous successes made in the DPRK have clearly proved the validity of the Songun policy pursued by Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The letter stressed that the participants of the seminar will contribute to accomplishing the cause of global independence by more dynamically pushing ahead with the drive to apply the Juche idea in conformity with the regional conditions and the specific situation of each country and nation.

Letter to Kim Jong Il Adopted in Uganda
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 10 (KCNA) -- A letter to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the joint seminar of Juche idea study groups in Uganda which was held in Kampala on Feb. 14 on the occasion of the February holiday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The letter said that at the seminar the members of the Ugandan National Committee for the Study of the Juche Idea had an in-depth discussion on the contents of the philosophical principle of the Juche idea, the originality of the Juche philosophy and the like, as well as the great feats performed by Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Through the seminar, the participants came to more deeply grasp the truthfulness, scientific accuracy and vitality of the Juche idea and realized once again that this idea is the only just guiding idea representing the era of independence, the letter noted, adding: We will deepen the study of the Juche idea and positively disseminate it, thus contributing to the realization of the cause of global independence.

Actions against Humiliating Agreement Called for in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 10 (KCNA) -- Representatives of political parties and civic and social organizations in south Korea reportedly called a joint press conference in front of the building of the "National Assembly" on Mar. 5 to protest against the handling of the special agreement on sharing the funds for the upkeep of the U.S. forces in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the press conference to be followed by the reading of a declaration opposing the NA's ratification of the special agreement signed by 1,325 figures from various circles. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that the "Committee of Unification, Foreign Affairs and Trade of the NA" brought the special agreement for discussion at the session of the NA after passing it on Mar. 2, the declaration warned that the NA would commit an indelible crime against the people if it is carried by its session. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The NA would be well advised to refuse to ratify the special agreement and adopt a resolution demanding the "government" renegotiate it with the U.S. though belatedly, it held. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The declaration expressed the determination to stage a movement for putting an end to the system for sharing those funds as an all-people movement.

All Koreans Called upon to Unite under Banner of "By Our Nation Itself"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 10 (KCNA) -- In order to make bigger progress in the on-going nationwide struggle to bring earlier the future of a reunified country all the Koreans should unite as one under the uplifted banner of "By our nation itself" and dynamically propel the process of reconciliation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Saturday observes this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the Koreans are to creditably fulfill their responsibility and role as a driving force for national reunification, they should single-mindedly unite under the banner of patriotism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the Koreans in the north and the south and overseas work together and achieve the great national unity on this basis, it will be possible to solve fundamental issues in achieving national reunification and this will help settle other matters with ease. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The period from the day the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration was adopted up to this date keenly convinced the Koreans that the great national unity is the only way for the nation to survive and achieve national reunification. The events and stirring realities that brought about by the Koreans in the movement for Korean reunification, guided by the idea "By our nation itself" are the results of the will of the Koreans to achieve unity and their ardent patriotic desire. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The split of the Korean nation is nothing but a temporary difficulty and misfortune recorded in the national history. It is the law governing the national development for the Korean nation to become one. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No force on earth can keep the homogenous Korean nation divided forever as it came into being and has developed throughout its history spanning 5,000 years and stem the trend of history towards reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The might of the united Korean nation is an engine for bringing about the dawn of national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Strong are the determination and enthusiasm of the Koreans to glorify the June 15 era of reunification by attaching importance to the nation, defending peace and achieving unity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a sacred and worthwhile struggle for bringing earlier national reunification to implement the above-said three tasks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Koreans in the north and the south and overseas should intensify their struggle to glorify the June 15 era of reunification full of conviction of sure victory and thus unroll a new history of peace and reunification on this land as early as possible, the article concludes.

Reception Given by Libyan Diplomatic Envoy
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 10 (KCNA) -- Bashir Ramadan Khalifa Abu Janah, secretary of the People's Bureau of the Great Socialist People's Libyan Arab Jamahiriya to the DPRK, hosted a reception at Pyongyang Koryo Hotel Friday on the occasion of the 30th anniversary of the proclamation of Jamahiriya in Libya. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Rim Kyong Man, minister of Foreign Trade, Kim Kyong Ho, first secretary of the Central Committee of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League, Mun Jae Chol, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, officials concerned and diplomatic envoys of various countries here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Staff members of the Libyan People's Bureau here were on hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the reception.

Preparations for WWIHC Completed in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 10 (KCNA) -- Full preparations for the 2007 World Women's Ice Hockey Championships (B Class) to be opened in the DPRK on March 17 have been completed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Kang Chol, vice secretary of the Korean Ice Hockey Association (KIHA) said this in an interview with KCNA.  He went on to say: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was decided at the annual general meeting of the International Ice Hockey Federation for 2005-2006 held last year that the DPRK will host the championships in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After then, the KIHA has made full preparation to host the championships successfully under the great care of the government and with its positive help. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We, first of all, checked all the game and training facilities and arranged and supplemented them with new ones in accordance with the technical requirements of international ice hockey ground. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The waiting rooms of players, medical section room, rooms for coaches and referees, physical training ground and subsidiary and training facilities are furnished at a high level. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Attention is being directed to providing every convenience to members and officials of the International Ice Hockey Federation and ice hockey teams so that they may spend pleasant days in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The IIHF delegate had visited the DPRK some time ago to acquaint himself with the preparation for the championships.  After looking round all the objects including the Ice Rink, he expressed satisfaction over the wonderful preparation and was grateful to officials concerned.

S. Korean Delegation Leaves 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 10 (KCNA) -- The delegation of the Committee for Peace in Northeast Asia of the Uri Party of south Korea led by Chairman Ri Hae Chan left here today after winding up its visit to Pyongyang on the invitation of the National Reconciliation Council of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was seen off at the airport by Choe Song Ik, vice-chairman of the council, and officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 While staying here, the delegation visited the Tower of the Juche Idea, the International Friendship Exhibition, Pyongyang Middle School No. 1, the U.S. imperialists' armed spy ship "Pueblo" and the Mansudae Art Studio. It also enjoyed art performance "Blue Sky over My Country" (Part Dawn) at the Pyongyang Indoor Stadium and had a conversation with Choe Sung Chol, vice-chairman of the Korea Asia-Pacific Peace Committee.

U.S. and S. Korean Warhawks' Anti-DPRK Saber-Rattling under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 10 (KCNA) -- RSOI and field mobile exercises the U.S. and the south Korean warlike forces are going to stage by mobilizing huge troops and the latest war hardware are a blatant challenge to the trend of the situation on the Korean Peninsula turning favorable and a serious provocation against the DPRK. A spokesman for the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland (CPRF) declared this in a statement on Saturday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The projected provocative saber-rattling is an uncouth act little short of leveling a gun at the dialogue partner and an anachronistic act aimed to stem the trend towards reconciliation and improved relations and restore the relations of confrontation and hostility. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The war maneuvers planned by the U.S. and the south Korean authorities, while saying one thing and doing another and playing double-dealing tactics, make the DPRK skeptical about whether they were sincere when they reached all the agreements with the DPRK and they are now willing to put them into practice. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A particular mention should be made of the fact that the authorities of the south side have perpetrated such perfidy as announcing the plan for such joint war exercises with the U.S. as soon as they went back after agreeing to exert common efforts to implement the February 13 agreement, ensure peace on the Korean Peninsula and improve the north-south relations, guided by the basic spirit of the June 15 joint declaration, at the recent ministerial talks. This behavior has touched off towering indignation of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. and the south Korean authorities should immediately cancel their plan to stage the anachronistic and reckless anti-DPRK saber-rattling, clearly understanding that the war moves will only becloud the prospect for the settlement of the nuclear issue on the Korean Peninsula and bring destruction.

All-out Anti-Japanese Struggle Called for in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, March 11 (KCNA) -- The Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration reportedly made public on March 6 a written warning to the Japanese government bent on cracking down upon Koreans in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the fact that the Japanese authorities and conservative forces are becoming more undisguised in their discrimination, suppression, threat and terrorism against Koreans in Japan, the written warning urged the Japanese authorities to come to their senses, though belatedly, and make an apology for Japan's past crimes and stop their discrimination and suppression of Koreans in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the Koreans will turn out in a dynamic anti-Japanese struggle should the Japanese authorities and ultra-right conservative forces fail to halt their crackdown upon Koreans in Japan, it declared.

Italia: obra de Kim Jong Il en folleto 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 10 de marzo (ATCC) -- Una Imprenta de Italia dio a luz el 16 de febrero en folleto la obra maestra del Dirigente Kim Jong Il "Materialicemos de modo consecuente el legado del gran Lider, camarada Kim Il Sung para la reunificacion de la patria", publicada el 4 de agosto del 86 (1997) de la Era Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Esta obra da cuenta de las inmortales hazanas del Presidente Kim Il Sung realizadas por la causa de reunificacion de la patria y formula en las 3 cartas para la misma los 3 principios de la reintegracion de la patria, el Proyecto de la Fundacion de la Republica Federal Democratica de Coryo y el Programa de diez Puntos para la Ggran Unidad Pannacional. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Igualmente, a base de ello, aclara las tareas y remedios para cumplir esa empresa mas importante para la nacion coreana.

Sri Lanka: foro regional asiatico sobre la autoconfianza
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 10 de marzo (ATCC) -- Tuvo lugar el 27 de febrero en Colombo el Foro Regional Asiatico sobre la Autoconfianza, la Economia Nacional y la Causa de Independencia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En la ocasion participaron el director general y el secretario general del Instituto Regional Asiatico de la Idea Juche, entre otras figuras. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Tambien se distinguia la delegacion de la Asociacion Coreana de Hombres de Ciencias Sociales. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al pronunciar las palabras de felicitacion, W. A. Duminduwardane, primer vicepresidente del Comite de Estudio de Autoconfianza (Juche) en Sri Lanka, dijo que bajo la bandera de la idea Juche y la del Songun (priorizacion militar) la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea avanza victoriosamente sin vacilacion alguna ante las maniobras norteamericanas en su contra manteniendo estrictamente el principio de apoyo en las propias fuerzas y destaco que hay que buscar en este foro las vias para aprender las experiencias del pueblo coreano. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al rendir el informe de la ocasion, el director general del Instituto Regional Asiatico de la Idea Juche, Reggie Ranatunge, senalo que construir un pais independiente como lo hizo el pueblo coreano es el deber comun de los pueblos progresistas del mundo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Tras resaltar que la autoconfianza de Corea esta fundamentada en la idea Juche, creada por el gran Lider, Presidente Kim Il Sung y profundizada y desarrollada por Su Excelencia Kim Jong Il, gran Dirigente, argumento la veracidad, la cientificidad y la vitalidad eterna de esta idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Harish Gupta, secretario general del mismo instituto, y otros oradores subrayaron que los paises regionales asiaticos deben levantar en lo mas alto la bandera de la independencia y de la autoconfianza y acotaron que para construir una poderosa economia nacional y cumplir la causa de independencia, es preciso frustrar las maniobras de "globalizacion" de EE.UU. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En el foro fue aprobada una carta dirigida al Dirigente Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La misiva senala que los ultimos exitos prodigiosos de Corea confirman claramente la justeza de la politica de Songun, que practica el Dirigente. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Subraya que los participantes en el seminario impulsaran con mas vigor las labores orientadas a materializar la idea Juche en lo conveniente a las caracteristicas regionales y las realidades de cada pais y nacion, de modo que contribuyeran al cumplimiento de la causa de la independencia en todo el orbe.

Unidad nacional es fuerza motriz de la reunificacion de Corea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 10 de marzo (ATCC) -- Para registrar un avance mas grande en la lucha pannacional de hoy por adelantar cuanto antes la reunificacion de la patria, todos los coreanos deben impulsar activa y unanimemente el proceso de reconciliacion bajo la bandera del ideal de "entre nosotros, los connacionales".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Adelanta el diario Rodong Sinmun en un articulo individual de este sabado y prosigue: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Todos los integrantes de la nacion coreana deben unirse con una sola voluntad bajo la bandera del patriotismo para cumplir su responsabilidad y papel, que les corresponden como sujetos de la reintegracion de la patria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Si todos los coreanos del Norte, el Sur y en ultramar alcanzan la gran unidad pannacional tras identificar sus decisiones, seran resueltos el problema fundamental para la mencionada empresa y los otros relativos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Desde el dia de la publicacion de la Declaracion Conjunta Norte-Sur del 15 de Junio hasta la fecha, los coreanos sintieron en carne propia que la gran unidad pannacional significa la unica salvacion para la nacion coreana e implica precisamente la reunificacion. La conmovedora realidad y los acontecimientos dados en el movimiento por la reintegracion territorial despues de la aparicion del ideal de "entre nosotros, los connacionales" son productos de la voluntad de todos los coreanos de unirse y de su fervoroso patriotismo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@La division de la patria es una tragedia temporal en la historia nacional y es una ley del desarrollo nacional que la nacion coreana sera fusionada en una sola. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Pues, ninguna fuerza puede dividir para siempre en dos partes a la homogenea nacion coreana, formada y desarrollada a traves de su larga historia de cinco milenios, ni frenar la corriente historica hacia la reunificacion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El motor de esta causa reside en las fuerzas unidas de la nacion coreana. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Son optimistas la determinacion y el entusiasmo de los coterraneos para hacer brillar la epoca de reunificacion iniciada el 15 de junio mediante la preponderancia de la nacion, la defensa de la paz y el logro de la union. La realizacion de estas tres tareas posibilita adelantar el dia de reunificacion de la patria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Con la firme confianza en la victoria, todos los coreanos del Norte, el Sur y en ultramar deben luchar con mas vigor por glorificar la epoca mencionada, y escribir cuanto antes en el territorio patrio una nueva historia de la paz y la reunificacion de la patria.
